## Write a program to convert feet to centimeters

1 foot = 30.48 centimeters

```txt
Input  : 5
Output : 152.4
```

---

<CodeBlock slug="convert-feet-to-centimeters" >

```c
#include <stdio.h> /*printf, scanf*/

double ConvertToCm(double feet);

int main()
{
    double feet = 0;

    if(1 != scanf("%lf",&feet))
    {
        return -1;
    }

    printf("%.1f\n",ConvertToCm(feet));

    return 0;
}


double ConvertToCm(double feet)
{
    return feet * 30.48;
}
```

